-- Bernanke, Paulson to brief Congress on crisis: CNBC
-- 
-- Thu Sep 18, 2008 5:34pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/18/us-financial-paulson-bernanke-idUSN1825814620080918

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - U.S. Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson and Federal Reserve Chairman Ben Bernanke will meet with congressional leaders on Thursday night to discuss possible solutions to the credit crisis, CNBC reported. 

 The meeting is with the full congressional leadership, CNBC said, citing one unnamed source. Fed and Treasury spokesman could not be immediately reached for comment. (Reporting by  Tim Ahmann ; Editing by Dan Grebler)